import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Delay')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['time'])
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Time')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between distance and time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance_range'] = pd.cut(data['distance'], bins=np.arange(0, data['distance'].max() + 100, 100))
    avg_delay_by_distance = data.groupby('distance_range')['delay'].mean().reset_index()

    plt.bar(avg_delay_by_distance['distance_range'].astype(str), avg_delay_by_distance['delay'])
    plt.xlabel('Distance Range')
    plt.ylabel('Average Delay')
    plt.title('What is the average delay for each distance range?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Average Delay'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay_range'] = pd.cut(data['delay'], bins=[-float('inf'), 0, 15, 30, 45, float('inf')], labels=['<0', '0-15', '15-30', '30-45', '>45'])
    avg_distance_per_delay_range = data.groupby('delay_range')['distance'].mean().reset_index()

    plt.bar(avg_distance_per_delay_range['delay_range'], avg_distance_per_delay_range['distance'])
    plt.xlabel('Delay Range (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Average Distance (miles)')
    plt.title('What is the average distance for each delay range?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Average Distance'], loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
